# Day 2 - Data Structures

## 📌 Objective
Learn the basics of Python data structures and how to store and manipulate data efficiently.

---

### 1. Lists
- Ordered and mutable collection
- Indexing and slicing
- Adding and removing elements

### 2. Tuples
- Ordered but immutable
- Used for fixed data

### 3. Sets
- Unordered collection
- Stores unique values only

### 4. Dictionaries
- Key-value pairs
- Used to store structured data

---

##  What I Practiced
- Created and modified lists
- Used tuples for fixed values
- Removed duplicates using sets
- Stored and accessed data using dictionaries

---


##  What I Learned
- Difference between data structures
- When to use each type
- Basic operations on each structure

---
